cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT

This paper deals with routing in ad hoc networks, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an Artificial Neural Network based model, which falls under the subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The model is non-deterministic, which involves probabilistic predictions, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed model also considers various parameters, which can be seen as a control system, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also involves simulation using OMNET++ simulator, which falls under the subfield of Information Theory (cs.IT).
